1
00:03:01,114 --> 00:03:02,844
She looks at me every day.

2
00:03:03,216 --> 00:03:04,796
Mary Jane Watson.

3
00:03:05,152 --> 00:03:08,691
Oh, boy. If she only knew
how I felt about her.

4
00:03:09,322 --> 00:03:10,932
But she can never know.

5
00:03:11,291 --> 00:03:14,251
! made a choice once to live
a life of responsibility.

6
00:03:14,995 --> 00:03:16,955
A life she can never be a part of.

7
00:03:17,364 --> 00:03:18,474
Who am I?

8
00:03:18,765 --> 00:03:21,105
I'm Spider-Man, given a job to do.

9
00:03:21,568 --> 00:03:24,198
And I'm Peter Parker,
and I, too, have a fob.

10
00:03:24,705 --> 00:03:26,135
Parker. Parker!

11
00:03:26,740 --> 00:03:28,470
No, no, no, stop! Stop!

12
00:03:30,243 --> 00:03:32,463
Parker, you're late, man. Always late.

13
00:03:33,113 --> 00:03:35,693
I'm sorry, Mr. Aziz.
There was a disturbance.

14
00:03:36,183 --> 00:03:38,113
Another disturbance.
Always a disturbance with you.

15
00:03:38,518 --> 00:03:41,008
Come on, 21 minutes ago,
in comes order.

16
00:03:41,488 --> 00:03:44,678
Harmattan, Burton & Smith.
Eight extra-large deep-dish pizzas.

17
00:03:45,292 --> 00:03:47,842
In eight minutes, ! am defaulting on
Joe's 29-minute guarantee.

18
00:03:48,328 --> 00:03:50,938
Then, not only am I receiving
no money for these pizzas...

19
00:03:51,431 --> 00:03:53,831
...but I will lose the customer forever
to Pizza Yurt.

20
00:03:54,301 --> 00:03:57,231
Look, you are my only hope, all right?
You have to make it in time.

21
00:03:57,771 --> 00:04:01,081
Peter, you're a nice guy.
But you're just not dependable.

22
00:04:02,075 --> 00:04:03,535
This is your last chance.

23
00:04:04,077 --> 00:04:08,117
You have to go 42 blocks
in 7 12 minutes or your ass is fired.

24
00:04:10,417 --> 00:04:12,087
Go!

25
00:04:34,574 --> 00:04:36,004
Hey, what, are you stupid?

26
00:04:58,165 --> 00:05:00,915
Whoa! He stole that guy's pizzas!

27
00:05:10,076 --> 00:05:11,366
I'm gonna get it!

28
00:05:27,227 --> 00:05:29,217
Hey, you guys.
No playing in the streets.

29
00:05:29,663 --> 00:05:30,863
Yes, Mr. Spider-Man.

30
00:05:31,298 --> 00:05:32,788
See you.

31
00:05:34,167 --> 00:05:35,217
Way to go, Spidey!

32
00:06:28,288 --> 00:06:29,958
Pizza time.

33
00:06:34,995 --> 00:06:36,285
You're late.

34
00:06:37,430 --> 00:06:38,540
I'm not paying for those.

35
00:06:57,250 --> 00:07:00,240
Joe's 29-minute guarantee
. .
IS a promise, man.

36
00:07:01,087 --> 00:07:04,957
I know to you, Parker, a promise
means nothing. But to me, it's serious.

37
00:07:05,659 --> 00:07:07,389
It's serious to me too, Mr. Aziz.

38
00:07:07,794 --> 00:07:10,014
-You're fired. Go.
-Please, I need this job.

39
00:07:10,463 --> 00:07:12,803
-You're fired.
-Look, give me another chance.

40
00:07:22,242 --> 00:07:23,382
You're fired.

41
00:07:24,010 --> 00:07:24,109
-Parker, hello. You're fired.
-Why?

42
00:07:24,110 --> 00:07:25,810
-Parker, hello. You're fired.
-Why?

43
00:07:26,179 --> 00:07:27,409
Dogs catching Frisbees?

44
00:07:27,714 --> 00:07:29,794
Pigeons in the park?
A couple geezers playing chess?

45
00:07:30,250 --> 00:07:31,270
-Boss.
-Not now.

46
00:07:31,584 --> 00:07:34,014
The Bugle could show another side
of New York for a change.

47
00:07:34,487 --> 00:07:37,097
We got six minutes to deadline, Jonah.
We need page one.

48
00:07:37,590 --> 00:07:40,659
I don't pay you to be a sensitive artiste.
Il pay you-- Still not now!

49
00:07:41,227 --> 00:07:43,417
l pay you because that psycho
Spider-Man will pose for you.

50
00:07:44,030 --> 00:07:47,049
He won't let me take any more pictures.
You turned the whole city against him.

51
00:07:47,600 --> 00:07:48,970
A fact I'm very proud of.

52
00:07:49,336 --> 00:07:52,676
Get your pretty little portfolio off my
desk before I go into a diabetic coma.

53
00:07:53,273 --> 00:07:56,173
-It's your wife, she lost her checkbook.
-Thanks for the good news.

54
00:07:56,743 --> 00:07:59,763
Please, isn't there any of these shots
you can use? I need the money.

55
00:08:01,481 --> 00:08:03,121
Miss Brant. Get me a violin.

56
00:08:03,483 --> 00:08:05,003
Five minutes to deadline, Jonah.

57
00:08:05,352 --> 00:08:07,751
Run a picture of a rancid chicken.
Here's the headline:

58
00:08:08,221 --> 00:08:09,891
"Food Poisoning Scare Sweeps City."

59
00:08:10,256 --> 00:08:12,275
-Some food got poisoned?
-I'm a little nauseous.

60
00:08:12,692 --> 00:08:14,362
All right, Mr. Jameson.

61
00:08:16,329 --> 00:08:18,199
It stinks.
Robbie, there's your page one.

62
00:08:18,631 --> 00:08:20,121
"Masked Menace Terrorizes Town."

63
00:08:20,467 --> 00:08:21,837
I told you, he's not a menace.

64
00:08:22,202 --> 00:08:23,602
-l told you--
-I'll take care of it.

65
00:08:24,104 --> 00:08:25,394
-I'll give you 150.
-Three hundred.

66
00:08:26,072 --> 00:08:27,152
That's outrageous.

67
00:08:27,440 --> 00:08:29,170
Done. Give this to the girl.

68
00:08:29,576 --> 00:08:30,626
Thank you. Bye-bye.

69
00:08:31,277 --> 00:08:32,537
Hi.

70
00:08:33,078 --> 00:08:34,279
Hey, Pete.

71
00:08:37,417 --> 00:08:40,787
I don't think this covers the advance
Il gave you a couple weeks ago.

72
00:08:41,554 --> 00:08:43,284
-Right.
-Sorry.

73
00:08:44,691 --> 00:08:45,891
Hey.

74
00:08:46,493 --> 00:08:47,893
Chin up, okay?

75
00:09:01,241 --> 00:09:02,441
Watch it, jerk!

76
00:09:13,319 --> 00:09:14,988
Dr. Connors. Sorry.

77
00:09:15,355 --> 00:09:16,815
Where were you headed, Parker?

78
00:09:17,223 --> 00:09:18,272
To your class.

79
00:09:18,558 --> 00:09:20,198
My class is over.

80
00:09:20,560 --> 00:09:22,459
See me standing here?

81
00:09:23,029 --> 00:09:26,249
I'm sorry. I'm trying.
l wanna be here.

82
00:09:27,033 --> 00:09:28,143
Then be here.

83
00:09:29,602 --> 00:09:30,972
Look at you, Peter.

84
00:09:31,604 --> 00:09:35,504
Your grades have been steadily
declining. You're late for class.

85
00:09:36,209 --> 00:09:38,758
You always appear exhausted.

86
00:09:40,480 --> 00:09:42,290
Your paper on fusion is still overdue.

87
00:09:42,682 --> 00:09:45,372
I know. I'm planning to write it
on Dr. Otto Octavius.

88
00:09:46,119 --> 00:09:48,839
Planning is not a major
at this university.

89
00:09:52,492 --> 00:09:54,242
Octavius is a friend of mine.

90
00:09:54,794 --> 00:09:56,544
Better do your research, Parker.

91
00:09:57,230 --> 00:09:59,980
Get it done, or I'm failing you.

92
00:10:21,721 --> 00:10:23,711
Surprise!

93
00:10:24,124 --> 00:10:25,854
Well, say something.

94
00:10:26,226 --> 00:10:27,306
What's the occasion?

95
00:10:27,594 --> 00:10:29,904
Really, Peter. It's your birthday!

96
00:10:30,663 --> 00:10:33,153
Whether you want
to remember it or not.

97
00:10:34,000 --> 00:10:36,840
He lives in another reality.
Don't you, Pete?

98
00:10:37,370 --> 00:10:39,100
-Hi, MJ.
-Hi.

99
00:10:39,739 --> 00:10:41,029
-Hey, buddy.
-Hey.

100
00:10:41,374 --> 00:10:42,394
Long time, no see.

101
00:10:43,476 --> 00:10:46,196
So how's the play?
l read a great review.

102
00:10:46,746 --> 00:10:48,266
It's going fine. It's going good.

103
00:10:48,615 --> 00:10:49,815
She's brilliant in it.

104
00:10:50,116 --> 00:10:51,486
Harry sent me roses.

105
00:10:51,985 --> 00:10:54,155
So where you been, pal?
You don't return my calls.

106
00:10:56,022 --> 00:10:57,542
I've been busy.

107
00:10:58,057 --> 00:11:01,097
Taking pictures of Spider-Man?
How's the bug these days?

108
00:11:01,661 --> 00:11:03,411
The less you see of that man,
the better.

109
00:11:03,796 --> 00:11:06,896
Now, let's all go into the other room
and have something to eat.

110
00:11:07,500 --> 00:11:08,550
I'll get the hors d'oeuvres.

111
00:11:09,035 --> 00:11:10,875
So how are things going at Oscorp?

112
00:11:11,271 --> 00:11:13,820
They're great.
I'm head of Special Projects.

113
00:11:14,307 --> 00:11:16,147
We're about to make
a breakthrough on fusion.

114
00:11:16,609 --> 00:11:20,239
How lovely, Harry. Your father
would be so proud, rest his soul.

115
00:11:21,047 --> 00:11:22,127
Thank you.

116
00:11:22,615 --> 00:11:25,895
We're actually funding
one of your idols, Pete. Otto Octavius.

117
00:11:26,486 --> 00:11:28,736
-I'm writing a paper on him.
-You want to meet him?

118
00:11:29,222 --> 00:11:30,271
You'd introduce me?

119
00:11:30,590 --> 00:11:33,370
You bet. Octavius is
gonna put Oscorp on the map...

120
00:11:34,060 --> 00:11:35,839
..in a way my father
never even dreamed of.

121
00:11:36,229 --> 00:11:37,929
M.J., could you give me a hand?

122
00:11:40,500 --> 00:11:41,960
She's waiting for you, pal.

123
00:11:42,735 --> 00:11:43,935
What do you mean?

124
00:11:44,237 --> 00:11:46,347
The way she looks at you
or doesn't look at you.

125
00:11:47,240 --> 00:11:48,380
However you want to look at it.

126
00:11:49,042 --> 00:11:50,912
I don't have time for girls right now.

127
00:11:51,311 --> 00:11:52,421
Why, are you dead?

128
00:11:52,745 --> 00:11:54,115
I've been kind of busy.

129
00:11:54,514 --> 00:11:56,004
Taking pictures of your friend?

130
00:11:57,584 --> 00:11:58,983
Could we get off that subject?

131
00:11:59,619 --> 00:12:02,229
l want us to be friends, Harry.
I want us to trust each other.

132
00:12:02,755 --> 00:12:04,215
Then be honest with me.

133
00:12:04,991 --> 00:12:07,040
If you knew who he was,
would you tell me?

134
00:12:31,017 --> 00:12:32,247
May.

135
00:12:32,585 --> 00:12:34,015
Oh, what, Ben?

136
00:12:35,488 --> 00:12:37,218
Wait.

137
00:12:37,624 --> 00:12:38,934
-Aunt May.
-Oh, my.

138
00:12:39,492 --> 00:12:44,031
Oh, Peter. Oh, for a second there,
l thought I was years ago.

139
00:12:47,033 --> 00:12:48,583
Everybody's gone, aren't they?

140
00:12:49,335 --> 00:12:50,825
Did they have a good time?

141
00:12:51,471 --> 00:12:52,551
I'm sure they did.

142
00:12:54,574 --> 00:12:57,944
-You okay?
-Of course. But you go home.

143
00:12:59,078 --> 00:13:03,588
And be careful. I don't like that
scooter thing you drive around.

144
00:13:04,350 --> 00:13:05,900
I'm worried about you.

145
00:13:06,552 --> 00:13:10,832
You're so alone.
And I saw the letter from the bank.

146
00:13:11,624 --> 00:13:13,874
Oh, my. You did?

147
00:13:14,627 --> 00:13:15,887
Oh, well.

148
00:13:16,195 --> 00:13:17,395
So?

149
00:13:18,197 --> 00:13:19,537
I'm a little behind.

150
00:13:20,767 --> 00:13:22,287
Everybody is.

151
00:13:23,269 --> 00:13:25,879
Anyway, I don't want
to talk about it anymore.

152
00:13:26,406 --> 00:13:29,715
I'm tired,
and you better start back home.

153
00:13:31,811 --> 00:13:34,061
Here, kiddo. Happy birthday.

154
00:13:34,747 --> 00:13:36,207
You need it more than I do.

155
00:13:36,549 --> 00:13:38,799
-No, I can't take that from you.
-Yes, you can!

156
00:13:39,285 --> 00:13:41,035
You can take this money from me.

157
00:13:41,454 --> 00:13:43,883
For God's sake, it's not much.
Now, take it!

158
00:13:44,357 --> 00:13:46,467
And don't you dare leave it here.

159
00:13:47,093 --> 00:13:48,793
Oh, I'm sorry.

160
00:13:50,196 --> 00:13:53,216
It's just that l miss
your uncle Ben so much.

161
00:13:55,702 --> 00:14:00,062
Can you believe that it's two years
next month since he was taken?

162
00:14:03,109 --> 00:14:05,009
I think to myself at times...

163
00:14:06,446 --> 00:14:10,136
.. were I to face the one responsible
for what happened, I'd....

164
00:14:11,684 --> 00:14:13,464
Oh, I don't know what I'd do.

165
00:14:20,326 --> 00:14:21,786
Now...

166
00:14:23,763 --> 00:14:26,193
.. you better take
the rest of your cake home.

167
00:14:41,347 --> 00:14:42,577
Hey.

168
00:14:43,082 --> 00:14:44,922
Hey. You're still here.

169
00:14:46,252 --> 00:14:47,592
l saw your billboard on Bleecker.

170
00:14:48,154 --> 00:14:50,964
Isn't it funny?
I'm really kind of embarrassed.

171
00:14:51,491 --> 00:14:55,091
Don't be. It's nice.
I get to see you every day now.

172
00:14:58,331 --> 00:15:00,351
I liked seeing you tonight, Peter.

173
00:15:03,002 --> 00:15:04,431
Oh, boy, yeah.

174
00:15:05,338 --> 00:15:07,918
"Oh, boy, yeah" what?

175
00:15:12,712 --> 00:15:14,202
Nothing.

176
00:15:18,618 --> 00:15:20,348
Do you want to say something?

177
00:15:26,592 --> 00:15:28,052


178
00:15:34,200 --> 00:15:35,280
. Was...

179
00:15:36,436 --> 00:15:39,276
.. wondering if you're still
in the Village.

180
00:15:48,781 --> 00:15:50,560
You're such a mystery.

181
00:16:01,160 --> 00:16:02,770
Peter.

182
00:16:04,330 --> 00:16:05,620
What?

183
00:16:10,770 --> 00:16:12,319
Happy birthday.

184
00:16:21,280 --> 00:16:23,150
I'm seeing somebody now.

185
00:16:24,083 --> 00:16:26,132
You mean, like a boyfriend?

186
00:16:26,552 --> 00:16:28,922
Well, like I like him.

187
00:16:32,458 --> 00:16:33,568
What?

188
00:16:34,594 --> 00:16:36,024
Nothing.

189
00:16:37,129 --> 00:16:39,939
That's good, you know?
Companionship....

190
00:16:42,068 --> 00:16:43,438
May be more than that.

191
00:16:44,704 --> 00:16:46,133
More?

192
00:16:47,139 --> 00:16:48,339
I don't know.

193
00:16:49,775 --> 00:16:51,855
I'm coming to see your play
tomorrow night.

194
00:16:55,181 --> 00:16:57,761
-You're coming?
-I'll be there.

195
00:16:59,085 --> 00:17:00,485
Don't disappoint me.

196
00:17:02,221 --> 00:17:03,561
I won't.

197
00:17:18,104 --> 00:17:19,364
Rent.

198
00:17:23,409 --> 00:17:25,809
-Hi.
-Hi. What's "hi"?

199
00:17:26,279 --> 00:17:27,539
Can I spend it?

200
00:17:28,513 --> 00:17:30,184
l have a paycheck due this week
and--

201
00:17:30,550 --> 00:17:33,570
-You're a month late again. Again.
-l promise as soon as--

202
00:17:34,253 --> 00:17:37,153
If promises were crackers,
my daughter would be fat.

203
00:17:38,224 --> 00:17:42,093
I'm really sorry, Mr. Ditkovitch. All l got
is this 20 for the rest of the week.

204
00:17:43,362 --> 00:17:44,622
"Sorry" doesn't pay the rent.

205
00:17:45,131 --> 00:17:49,441
And don't try to sneak past me. I have
ears like a cat and eyes like a rodent.

206
00:17:51,604 --> 00:17:54,154
-Thanks, Mr. Ditkovitch.
-Hi, Pete.

207
00:18:41,320 --> 00:18:42,780
Hello?

208
00:18:50,329 --> 00:18:51,849
Rent?

209
00:18:57,169 --> 00:18:59,189
Doctor? Mr. Osborn's here.

210
00:18:59,605 --> 00:19:03,065
Nobel Prize, Otto. Nobel Prize.
And we'll all be rich.

211
00:19:03,776 --> 00:19:05,266
It's not about the prizes, Harry.

212
00:19:05,611 --> 00:19:07,221
But you need money.
You need Oscorp.

213
00:19:07,613 --> 00:19:08,843
Who do we have here?

214
00:19:09,148 --> 00:19:10,548
This is my good friend
I called you about.

215
00:19:11,050 --> 00:19:12,389
He got me through
high-school science.

216
00:19:12,752 --> 00:19:15,361
Peter Parker, sir.
I'm writing a paper on you for--

217
00:19:16,055 --> 00:19:17,255
I know what you're doing here...

218
00:19:17,556 --> 00:19:19,516
.. but I don't have time
to talk to students now.

219
00:19:20,760 --> 00:19:22,400
But Oscorp pays the bills, so...

220
00:19:22,762 --> 00:19:24,902
That's why I have to take off.
Board meeting.

221
00:19:25,331 --> 00:19:28,261
But my job is done here.
Got you two geniuses together.

222
00:19:28,801 --> 00:19:32,900
Good luck tomorrow, Otto.
Nobel Prize. We'll see you in Sweden!

223
00:19:36,242 --> 00:19:37,472
Interesting fellow, your friend.

224
00:19:38,344 --> 00:19:39,834
l won't take much of your time.

225
00:19:40,212 --> 00:19:43,962
Now I remember you. You're Connorsâ€™
student. He tells me you're brilliant.

226
00:19:45,317 --> 00:19:47,127
He also tells me you're lazy.

227
00:19:48,421 --> 00:19:49,441
I'm trying to do better.

228
00:19:49,755 --> 00:19:52,975
Being brilliant's not enough,
young man. You have to work hard.

229
00:19:53,693 --> 00:19:56,593
Intelligence is not a privilege,
it's a gift.

230
00:19:57,163 --> 00:19:59,003
And you use it
for the good of mankind.

231
00:19:59,398 --> 00:20:00,628
You want to try it back there?

232
00:20:01,667 --> 00:20:03,097
So is that it?

233
00:20:03,436 --> 00:20:07,245
Yes. My design to initiate
and sustain fusion.

234
00:20:08,307 --> 00:20:10,857
l understand you use harmonics
of atomic frequencies.

235
00:20:11,343 --> 00:20:12,483
Sympathetic frequencies.

236
00:20:12,778 --> 00:20:14,558
Harmonic reinforcement?

237
00:20:15,281 --> 00:20:16,801
Go on.

238
00:20:17,483 --> 00:20:20,643
An exponential increase
in energy output.

239
00:20:21,253 --> 00:20:22,592
A huge amount of energy.

240
00:20:23,122 --> 00:20:26,752
Like a perpetual sun providing
renewable power for the whole world.

241
00:20:27,393 --> 00:20:30,203
Are you sure you could stabilize
the fusion reaction?

242
00:20:30,730 --> 00:20:33,750
Peter, what have we been talking
about for the last hour and a half?

243
00:20:34,734 --> 00:20:36,374
This is my life's work.

244
00:20:37,002 --> 00:20:39,812
l certainly know the consequences
of the slightest miscalculation.

245
00:20:40,339 --> 00:20:42,269
I'm sorry. I didn't mean
to question you.

246
00:20:42,708 --> 00:20:45,748
Rosie, our new friend thinks
I'm gonna blow up the city.

247
00:20:46,345 --> 00:20:47,955
You can sleep soundly tonight.

248
00:20:48,314 --> 00:20:49,834
Otto's done his homework.

249
00:20:50,216 --> 00:20:52,906
Come to the demonstration tomorrow,
and you'll see for yourself.

250
00:20:53,686 --> 00:20:55,735
And you need
to sleep soundly tonight, Otto.

251
00:20:56,155 --> 00:20:58,024
Did Edison sleep
before he turned on the light?

252
00:20:58,691 --> 00:21:00,831
Did Marconi sleep
before he turned on the radio?

253
00:21:01,293 --> 00:21:03,132
Did Beethoven sleep
before he wrote the 5th?

254
00:21:03,529 --> 00:21:06,399
Did Bernoulli sleep before he found
the curves of quickest descent?

255
00:21:07,099 --> 00:21:09,208
Rosie, I love this boy.

256
00:21:09,668 --> 00:21:13,007
Peter, tell us about yourself.
Do you have a girlfriend?

257
00:21:14,540 --> 00:21:15,970
Well...

258
00:21:17,243 --> 00:21:18,413
I don't really know.

259
00:21:18,744 --> 00:21:21,434
Well, shouldn't you know?
Il mean, who would know?

260
00:21:22,181 --> 00:21:24,761
Leave him alone.
Maybe it's a secret love.

261
00:21:25,251 --> 00:21:26,951
Love should never be a secret.

262
00:21:27,319 --> 00:21:30,158
If you keep something as complicated
as love stored up inside...

263
00:21:31,323 --> 00:21:32,813
..gonna make you sick.

264
00:21:33,526 --> 00:21:35,166
I finally got lucky in love.

265
00:21:35,528 --> 00:21:36,818
We both did.

266
00:21:37,129 --> 00:21:40,259
But it's hardly perfect.
You have to work at it.

267
00:21:41,033 --> 00:21:44,163
I met him on the college steps,
and I knew it wasn't going to be easy.

268
00:21:44,737 --> 00:21:47,727
He was studying science,
and I was studying English literature.

269
00:21:48,274 --> 00:21:51,024
That's right. 1 was trying to explain
the theory of relativity.

270
00:21:51,577 --> 00:21:53,827
And Rosie was trying
to explain T.S. Eliot.

271
00:21:55,414 --> 00:21:57,084
I still don't understand
what he was talking about.

272
00:21:57,449 --> 00:21:58,499
-Yes, you do.
-I'm serious.

273
00:21:58,784 --> 00:22:01,944
T.S. Eliot is more complicated
than advanced science.

274
00:22:03,055 --> 00:22:06,515
But if you want to get a woman to fall
in love with you, feed her poetry.

275
00:22:07,359 --> 00:22:08,408
Poetry.

276
00:22:10,095 --> 00:22:11,145
Never fails.

277
00:22:15,768 --> 00:22:18,348
A tall and slender maiden
All alone upon a prairie

278
00:22:19,038 --> 00:22:21,058
Brightest green were all her garments

279
00:22:21,473 --> 00:22:23,493
And her hair was like the sunshine

280
00:22:24,276 --> 00:22:26,676
Day by day he gazed upon her

281
00:23:24,203 --> 00:23:25,513
Rent!

282
00:23:27,640 --> 00:23:29,160
Where is my money?!

283
00:23:55,100 --> 00:23:57,060
You seem jittery tonight.

284
00:23:57,503 --> 00:23:59,082
You never know who's coming.

285
00:24:14,586 --> 00:24:17,196
Ladies, five minutes. Five minutes.

286
00:24:34,740 --> 00:24:36,000
How'd you do that?

287
00:24:39,178 --> 00:24:41,138
Work out, plenty of rest.

288
00:24:41,613 --> 00:24:43,283
You know, eat your green vegetables.

289
00:24:44,383 --> 00:24:47,573
That's what my mom is always saying.
I just never actually believed her.

290
00:24:50,689 --> 00:24:51,979
Come on. Go.

291
00:24:55,127 --> 00:24:56,297
Keep it steady.

292
00:25:19,051 --> 00:25:20,281
It's a web.

293
00:25:21,520 --> 00:25:23,040
Go, Spidey, go!

294
00:25:31,296 --> 00:25:32,406
We got trouble!

295
00:25:51,250 --> 00:25:52,980
Get me down!

296
00:25:53,786 --> 00:25:56,306
lam more than content
with what Mr. Moncrieff said.

297
00:25:56,789 --> 00:25:59,809
His voice alone inspires one
with absolute credulity.

298
00:26:00,359 --> 00:26:02,198
Then you think we should
forgive them?

299
00:26:05,364 --> 00:26:06,884
Yes.

300
00:26:07,533 --> 00:26:08,902
I mean, no.

301
00:26:13,372 --> 00:26:17,062
Hey. Hey. Hey, chief.
You park there, I'm towing it.

302
00:26:18,310 --> 00:26:19,419
Whatever.

303
00:26:22,281 --> 00:26:23,571
Shoelace.

304
00:26:28,320 --> 00:26:29,810
You might want to....

305
00:26:35,360 --> 00:26:38,959
-Can I help you?
-Yeah, I've come to see the show.

306
00:26:39,631 --> 00:26:43,001
Oh, I'm sorry, sir. No one will be
seated after the doors are closed.

307
00:26:44,670 --> 00:26:46,780
It helps maintain the illusion.

308
00:26:48,373 --> 00:26:51,333
Miss Watson, she's a friend of mine.
She asked me to come.

309
00:26:52,044 --> 00:26:53,274
But not to come late.

310
00:26:55,814 --> 00:26:58,914
I have to see this show.
Just let me in, I'll stand in the--

311
00:27:12,297 --> 00:27:14,877
A Spider-Man
A Spider-Man

312
00:27:15,367 --> 00:27:17,997
A-does whatever a spider can

313
00:27:18,537 --> 00:27:21,147
A-spins a web, any size

314
00:27:21,673 --> 00:27:23,843
Catches thieves a-just like flies

315
00:27:24,276 --> 00:27:27,086
Look out
Here comes the Spider-Man

316
00:27:43,328 --> 00:27:45,498
You sure you don't wanna
come tonight?

317
00:27:46,131 --> 00:27:47,271
Yeah, I'm sure.

318
00:27:47,566 --> 00:27:49,266
-Okay. Call me.
-I will.

319
00:27:49,635 --> 00:27:51,185
-You were great tonight.
-Thanks.

320
00:27:53,805 --> 00:27:56,145
May I have an autograph,
please, miss?

321
00:27:57,743 --> 00:27:59,003
What are you doing here?

322
00:28:14,259 --> 00:28:15,309
You hungry?

323
00:28:15,594 --> 00:28:16,644
Starved.

324
00:29:07,446 --> 00:29:09,196
What was that?

325
00:29:13,785 --> 00:29:15,365
Okay.

326
00:29:55,193 --> 00:29:56,503
Cool Spidey outfit.

327
00:29:58,563 --> 00:29:59,613
Thanks.

328
00:30:01,767 --> 00:30:02,997
Where'd you get it?

329
00:30:04,436 --> 00:30:05,545
I made it.

330
00:30:09,741 --> 00:30:11,171
Looks uncomfortable.

331
00:30:12,644 --> 00:30:14,514
Yeah, it gets kind of itchy.

332
00:30:18,083 --> 00:30:20,773
And it rides up in the crotch
a little bit too.

333
00:31:12,537 --> 00:31:14,937
Hi. It's me.
Sing your song at the beep.

334
00:31:16,174 --> 00:31:17,224
Hi, M.J.

335
00:31:17,509 --> 00:31:18,589
This is Peter.

336
00:31:19,378 --> 00:31:22,038
l was on my way to your show and....

337
00:31:23,682 --> 00:31:26,752
Well, was on my bike...

338
00:31:30,188 --> 00:31:31,448
Are you there?

339
00:31:34,326 --> 00:31:36,876
really was planning on it all day.

340
00:31:38,463 --> 00:31:39,893
And...

341
00:31:41,433 --> 00:31:43,423
.. 1 know you predicted
I'd disappoint you.

342
00:31:44,169 --> 00:31:45,479
Bingo.

343
00:31:46,705 --> 00:31:48,225
It's amazing, isn't it?

344
00:31:49,374 --> 00:31:51,894
How complicated a simple thing...

345
00:31:53,412 --> 00:31:56,982
...like being someplace at 8:00
can become.

346
00:32:01,319 --> 00:32:04,799
Actually, there was
this obnoxious usher.

347
00:32:05,991 --> 00:32:08,741
Somebody has to talk
to that usher, M.J.

348
00:32:09,261 --> 00:32:10,521
Your time has expired.

349
00:32:10,996 --> 00:32:14,686
Please deposit 50 cents
for the next five minutes.

350
00:32:24,810 --> 00:32:26,770
l wanna tell you the truth.

351
00:32:29,181 --> 00:32:30,381
Here it is.

352
00:32:31,550 --> 00:32:33,010
I'm Spider-Man.

353
00:32:34,386 --> 00:32:35,526
Weird, huh?

354
00:32:37,589 --> 00:32:39,698
Now you know
why I can't be with you.

355
00:32:41,126 --> 00:32:45,106
If my enemies found out about you...

356
00:32:48,533 --> 00:32:51,342
. if you got hurt,
l could never forgive myself.

357
00:32:57,642 --> 00:33:00,272
I wish I could tell you
how I feel about you.

358
00:33:12,224 --> 00:33:13,303
Ladies and gentlemen...

359
00:33:13,592 --> 00:33:16,992
..my wife Rosie and I would like to
welcome you this afternoon.

360
00:33:17,596 --> 00:33:19,086
But first, before we start...

361
00:33:19,464 --> 00:33:23,244
..has anybody lost a large roll
of 20-dollar bills in a rubber band?

362
00:33:24,302 --> 00:33:25,532
Because we found the rubber band.

363
00:33:30,442 --> 00:33:31,642
It's a terrible joke.

364
00:33:32,110 --> 00:33:33,540
But thank you for coming.

365
00:33:34,179 --> 00:33:35,229
Today...

366
00:33:35,514 --> 00:33:39,524
.. you will witness the birth
of a new fusion-based energy source.

367
00:33:40,352 --> 00:33:44,892
Safe, renewable energy
and cheap electricity for everyone.

368
00:33:46,791 --> 00:33:49,781
And now let me introduce
my assistants.

369
00:33:57,702 --> 00:34:00,332
These four actuators were
developed and programmed...

370
00:34:01,039 --> 00:34:03,999
..for the sole purpose of creating
successful fusion.

371
00:34:04,576 --> 00:34:06,856
They are impervious to heat
and magnetism.

372
00:34:51,723 --> 00:34:55,942
These smart arms are controlled
by my brain through a neural link.

373
00:34:57,262 --> 00:34:59,752
Nanowires feed directly
into my cerebellum...

374
00:35:00,231 --> 00:35:03,831
.. allowing me to use these arms
to control fusion reaction...

375
00:35:04,469 --> 00:35:06,989
..in an environment
no human hand could enter.

376
00:35:07,472 --> 00:35:09,692
Doctor, if the artificial intelligence
in the arms...

377
00:35:10,141 --> 00:35:11,601
.. 1S as advanced as you suggest...

378
00:35:12,110 --> 00:35:13,890
.. couldn't that make you
vulnerable to them?

379
00:35:14,279 --> 00:35:15,359
How right you are.

380
00:35:15,647 --> 00:35:17,427
Which is why I developed
this inhibitor chip...

381
00:35:17,983 --> 00:35:20,003
...to protect
my higher brain function.

382
00:35:20,418 --> 00:35:24,428
It means I maintain control of these
arms, instead of them controlling me.

383
00:35:25,657 --> 00:35:27,297
And now on to the main event.

384
00:35:27,659 --> 00:35:29,359
Give me the blue light, Rosie.

385
00:35:49,280 --> 00:35:52,650
Precious tritium is the fuel
that makes this project go.

386
00:35:53,251 --> 00:35:56,001
There's only 25 pounds of it
on the whole planet.

387
00:35:57,088 --> 00:36:00,748
I'd like to thank Harry Osborn and
Oscorp Industries for providing it.

388
00:36:01,459 --> 00:36:03,069
Happy to pay the bills, Otto.

389
00:36:17,208 --> 00:36:18,438
Ladies and gentlemen...

390
00:36:21,279 --> 00:36:22,889
.. fasten your seat belts.

391
00:36:41,766 --> 00:36:44,076
Doctor, we have
a successful fusion reaction.

392
00:36:49,240 --> 00:36:52,109
This is a breakthrough
beyond your father's dreams.

393
00:36:52,644 --> 00:36:53,843
Thank you.

394
00:36:54,145 --> 00:36:55,845
We're producing
a thousand-megawatt surplus.

395
00:37:03,621 --> 00:37:05,261
The power of the sun...

396
00:37:06,191 --> 00:37:08,031
..in the palm of my hand.

397
00:37:29,981 --> 00:37:32,151
Keep calm! It's only a spike!

398
00:37:32,584 --> 00:37:34,223
It'll soon stabilize!

399
00:37:40,191 --> 00:37:42,680
Ladies and gentlemen,
please clear the room.

400
00:37:48,700 --> 00:37:50,009
We have a containment breach!

401
00:37:52,771 --> 00:37:54,761
Otto, please get back!

402
00:37:56,040 --> 00:37:58,410
Shut it off, Otto! Shut it off!

403
00:37:59,210 --> 00:38:01,400
It will stabilize! It's under control!

404
00:38:02,046 --> 00:38:03,535
I'm in charge here!

405
00:38:04,048 --> 00:38:06,417
It's my money! I'm in con--

406
00:38:10,421 --> 00:38:12,171
This doesn't change anything.

407
00:38:15,660 --> 00:38:17,879
-What are you doing?
-Pulling the plug.

408
00:38:18,530 --> 00:38:19,580
No!

409
00:38:38,683 --> 00:38:40,113
Rosie!

410
00:39:11,015 --> 00:39:12,065
Watch it.

411
00:39:12,350 --> 00:39:13,400
That was too close.

412
00:39:13,685 --> 00:39:17,255
If he had more than a drop of tritium,
he could have destroyed the city.

413
00:39:23,261 --> 00:39:24,431
I'm ruined.

414
00:39:26,331 --> 00:39:28,441
l have nothing left,
except Spider-Man.

415
00:39:29,033 --> 00:39:30,403
He saved your life, sir.

416
00:39:31,135 --> 00:39:33,185
He humiliated me by touching me.

417
00:39:33,605 --> 00:39:35,945
The press will be here soon.
l suggest we move on.

418
00:39:36,407 --> 00:39:38,107
What was he doing here anyway?

419
00:39:54,692 --> 00:39:56,882
Molten metal penetrated
the spinal cavity...

420
00:39:57,328 --> 00:39:59,198
..and fused the vertebrae
at multiple points...

421
00:39:59,597 --> 00:40:01,907
.. including the lamina
and the roof of the spinal column.

422
00:40:02,367 --> 00:40:04,237
We won't know the extent of
the damage until we get in there.

423
00:40:04,669 --> 00:40:07,279
l suggest we cut off these mechanical
arms, slice up the harness...

424
00:40:07,772 --> 00:40:09,942
..and, if need be,
consider a laminectomy...

425
00:40:10,408 --> 00:40:13,218
.. With posterior spinal fusion
from C7-T1 to T12.

426
00:40:14,012 --> 00:40:15,092
We're ready, doctor.

427
00:40:18,483 --> 00:40:20,123
Anybody here take shop class?

428
00:41:03,161 --> 00:41:05,151
Help me! Help me!

429
00:42:16,501 --> 00:42:19,631
No!

430
00:43:11,456 --> 00:43:13,976
It's all over town, Robbie.
Gossip. Rumors.

431
00:43:14,492 --> 00:43:16,362
Panic in the streets, if we're lucky.

432
00:43:16,761 --> 00:43:19,250
Crazy scientist turns himself
into some kind of a monster.

433
00:43:19,730 --> 00:43:22,360
Four mechanical arms welded
right onto his body.

434
00:43:23,301 --> 00:43:27,431
Guy named Otto Octavius winds up
with eight limbs. What are the odds?

435
00:43:28,172 --> 00:43:29,222
Hoffman!

436
00:43:31,409 --> 00:43:32,579
What are we gonna call this guy?

437
00:43:33,077 --> 00:43:35,007
-"Dr. Octopus."
-That's crap.

438
00:43:35,446 --> 00:43:36,816
-"Science Squid"?
-Crap!

439
00:43:37,548 --> 00:43:39,037
-"Dr. Strange."
-That's pretty good.

440
00:43:40,084 --> 00:43:43,743
But it's taken.
Wait, wait! I got it. "Dr. Octopus."

441
00:43:45,089 --> 00:43:46,459
-I like it.
-Of course you do.

442
00:43:46,791 --> 00:43:50,131
Dr. Octopus. New villain in town.
"Doc Ock."

443
00:43:50,728 --> 00:43:52,478
-Genius.
-What, are you looking for a raise?

444
00:43:53,030 --> 00:43:54,400
Get out.

445
00:43:55,366 --> 00:43:56,416
Chief, found Parker.

446
00:43:56,701 --> 00:43:58,751
Where you been?
Why don't you pay your phone bill.

447
00:43:59,203 --> 00:44:01,163
Mad scientist goes berserk,
we don't have pictures!

448
00:44:01,572 --> 00:44:02,832
l heard Spider-Man was there.

449
00:44:04,142 --> 00:44:06,332
Where were you?
Photographing squirrels? You're fired.

450
00:44:06,777 --> 00:44:08,037
Chief, the planetarium party.

451
00:44:08,346 --> 00:44:09,836
You're un-fired.
I need you, come here.

452
00:44:10,214 --> 00:44:11,504
What do you know
about high society?

453
00:44:11,983 --> 00:44:13,973
-Oh. Well, I--
-Don't answer that.

454
00:44:14,385 --> 00:44:17,345
My society photographer got hit in the
head by a polo ball. You're all I got.

455
00:44:18,055 --> 00:44:20,665
Big party for an American hero.
My son, the astronaut.

456
00:44:21,159 --> 00:44:22,589
Could you pay me in advance?

457
00:44:32,036 --> 00:44:34,086
You serious? Pay you for what?
Standing there?

458
00:44:34,539 --> 00:44:36,909
The planetarium, tomorrow night,
8:00. There's the door.

459
00:44:52,290 --> 00:44:53,870
My Rosie's dead.

460
00:44:56,227 --> 00:44:57,807
My dream is dead.

461
00:45:01,632 --> 00:45:02,832
And these...

462
00:45:05,036 --> 00:45:08,026
.. monstrous things should be
at the bottom of the river...

463
00:45:11,309 --> 00:45:12,479
.. along with me.

464
00:45:21,586 --> 00:45:23,046
Something...

465
00:45:24,655 --> 00:45:26,055
..in my head.

466
00:45:29,994 --> 00:45:31,284
Something talking.

467
00:45:35,499 --> 00:45:36,839
The inhibitor chip!

468
00:45:40,371 --> 00:45:41,801
Gone.

469
00:45:46,677 --> 00:45:47,907
Rebuild.

470
00:45:51,415 --> 00:45:52,904
No.

471
00:45:54,285 --> 00:45:55,484
Peter was right.

472
00:45:58,122 --> 00:45:59,412
I miscalculated.

473
00:46:06,264 --> 00:46:08,044
l couldn't have miscalculated.

474
00:46:09,400 --> 00:46:11,130
It was working, wasn't it?

475
00:46:16,274 --> 00:46:17,444
Yes.

476
00:46:18,676 --> 00:46:21,306
We could rebuild.
Enlarge the containment field.

477
00:46:21,812 --> 00:46:23,892
Make it bigger
and stronger than ever.

478
00:46:25,082 --> 00:46:26,542
But we need money.

479
00:46:28,586 --> 00:46:29,846
Steal it?

480
00:46:30,154 --> 00:46:31,794
No, no, no, I'm not a criminal.

481
00:46:34,525 --> 00:46:35,635
That's right.

482
00:46:37,728 --> 00:46:40,688
The real crime would be not to finish
what we started.

483
00:46:44,635 --> 00:46:46,125
We'll do it here.

484
00:46:47,104 --> 00:46:49,973
The power of the sun
in the palm of my hand.

485
00:46:50,608 --> 00:46:52,888
Nothing will stand in our way.

486
00:46:53,344 --> 00:46:54,454
Nothing!

487
00:47:00,117 --> 00:47:02,307
-That's the social security.
-Yes, l see.

488
00:47:03,054 --> 00:47:04,424
My uncle Ben's life insurance.

489
00:47:04,789 --> 00:47:06,839
Yes, but I'm afraid...

490
00:47:07,291 --> 00:47:09,981
. it's just not sufficient
to refinance your home.

491
00:47:10,628 --> 00:47:13,758
Oh, but I'm giving
piano lessons again.

492
00:47:14,365 --> 00:47:15,444
You are?

493
00:47:20,705 --> 00:47:23,665
We appreciate
that you've just opened up...

494
00:47:24,241 --> 00:47:26,411
..a new supersaver account
with us today.

495
00:47:27,044 --> 00:47:28,094
But the fact is...

496
00:47:28,412 --> 00:47:32,131
.. you do not have the assets
to justify this loan. I'm sorry.

497
00:47:33,351 --> 00:47:34,781
Well...

498
00:47:36,620 --> 00:47:38,259
At least we get the toaster.

499
00:47:38,622 --> 00:47:42,162
Actually, that's only
with a deposit of 300 or more.

500
00:47:45,529 --> 00:47:46,819
Oh, yes, I see.

501
00:47:48,366 --> 00:47:49,856
Okay.

502
00:47:53,137 --> 00:47:54,947
Don't worry, we'll figure it out.

503
00:48:12,456 --> 00:48:13,596
Peter?

504
00:48:15,526 --> 00:48:17,306
Don't leave me.

505
00:48:18,396 --> 00:48:20,476
Oh, that boy of yours is a real hero.

506
00:48:21,365 --> 00:48:22,384
Hold it!

507
00:48:23,367 --> 00:48:25,737
Put your arms up! All of them!

508
00:48:49,326 --> 00:48:50,406
Here's your change!

509
00:49:00,538 --> 00:49:01,968
Oh, no. Come on!

510
