I'll give you all the tritium you need.

770
01:16:12,435 --> 01:16:15,865
On second thought,
bring him to me alive.

771
01:16:16,472 --> 01:16:17,552
How do I find him?

772
01:16:19,075 --> 01:16:20,445
-Peter Parker.
-Parker?

773
01:16:20,776 --> 01:16:22,946
He takes pictures of Spider-Man
for the Bugle.

774
01:16:23,379 --> 01:16:24,579
Make him tell you where he is.

775
01:16:30,553 --> 01:16:31,813
Have it ready.

776
01:16:35,658 --> 01:16:37,088
Don't hurt Peter!

777
01:16:50,506 --> 01:16:52,726
Somebody, help!

778
01:16:53,809 --> 01:16:55,269
Fire!

779
01:17:03,619 --> 01:17:06,228
Alisa, the Chens can't find their
daughter. Have you seen her?

780
01:17:08,124 --> 01:17:10,294
Somebody call the fire department!
Help!

781
01:17:11,427 --> 01:17:13,387
-Help!
-ls anybody in that building?

782
01:17:13,996 --> 01:17:16,166
We think there's a kid
stuck on the second floor.

783
01:17:16,699 --> 01:17:18,188
Hey, where you going?!

784
01:17:39,555 --> 01:17:40,865
I'm coming!

785
01:18:05,481 --> 01:18:07,971
It's okay. It's okay. Come here.
I'm gonna get you out of here.

786
01:18:08,450 --> 01:18:10,730
Come on. Come on.

787
01:19:11,247 --> 01:19:12,997
Mama.

788
01:19:25,261 --> 01:19:26,551
You got some guts, kid.

789
01:19:27,029 --> 01:19:30,979
Some poor soul got trapped
on the fourth floor. Never made it out.

790
01:19:31,767 --> 01:19:33,137
Oh, man.

791
01:19:36,238 --> 01:19:39,228
All right, Billy, let's knock it down
and roll them up. Get on out of here.

792
01:19:39,775 --> 01:19:43,205
Let's pick it up! Let's get all this
equipment, let's go! Let's move it!

793
01:19:49,418 --> 01:19:52,027
Am I not supposed to have
what I want?

794
01:19:53,422 --> 01:19:54,621
What I need?

795
01:19:57,259 --> 01:19:59,339
What am I supposed to do?

796
01:20:06,368 --> 01:20:07,628
I shouldn't have without...

797
01:20:08,504 --> 01:20:09,554
.. knocking.

798
01:20:14,376 --> 01:20:15,836
Come in.

799
01:20:19,081 --> 01:20:21,191
-Hi.
-Hi.

800
01:20:25,220 --> 01:20:27,410
Would you like a piece
of chocolate cake?

801
01:20:29,725 --> 01:20:30,955
Okay.

802
01:20:32,628 --> 01:20:34,178
And a glass of milk?

803
01:20:37,466 --> 01:20:38,926
That would be nice.

804
01:20:41,070 --> 01:20:42,910
Okay.

805
01:21:03,325 --> 01:21:04,965
Thank you.

806
01:21:09,998 --> 01:21:11,288
You got a message.

807
01:21:12,634 --> 01:21:14,004
It's your aunt.

808
01:21:14,336 --> 01:21:15,916
Thanks.

809
01:21:32,187 --> 01:21:33,297
What's going on?

810
01:21:33,622 --> 01:21:36,992
Oh, they gave me another few weeks,
but I decided the hell with it.

811
01:21:37,593 --> 01:21:40,843
I'm moving on.
l found a small apartment.

812
01:21:41,497 --> 01:21:42,807
Why didn't you tell me?

813
01:21:43,165 --> 01:21:46,005
I'm quite able
to take care of things myself.

814
01:21:46,535 --> 01:21:49,605
And Henry Jackson across
the street is giving me a hand...

815
01:21:50,205 --> 01:21:51,434
..and I'm giving him $5.

816
01:21:51,740 --> 01:21:53,200
That's Henry Jackson?

817
01:21:54,143 --> 01:21:55,953
Yes. It's funny what happens
in two years.

818
01:21:56,478 --> 01:21:59,548
Nine years old, has great ambitions.

819
01:22:01,550 --> 01:22:04,300
Listen, about my last visit...

820
01:22:05,120 --> 01:22:07,110
Pish-posh, we needn't talk about it.

821
01:22:07,523 --> 01:22:11,593
It's water over the dam or under
the bridge or wherever you like it.

822
01:22:15,564 --> 01:22:18,934
But you made a brave move
in telling me the truth.

823
01:22:19,601 --> 01:22:21,271
And I'm proud of you.

824
01:22:22,538 --> 01:22:24,727
And I thank you, and I....

825
01:22:26,275 --> 01:22:28,295
I love you, Peter.

826
01:22:29,745 --> 01:22:32,025
So very, very much.

827
01:22:51,733 --> 01:22:54,363
Hey. Where are all my comic books?

828
01:22:55,037 --> 01:22:57,647
Those dreadful things?
I gave those away.

829
01:23:01,009 --> 01:23:03,819
-I put the pans in the box, Mrs. Parker.
-Thank you, Henry.

830
01:23:04,346 --> 01:23:05,606
-Hi, Peter.
-Hey, Henry.

831
01:23:06,148 --> 01:23:07,228
You're getting tall.

832
01:23:07,549 --> 01:23:11,119
Henry, why don't you put those
cookbooks in with the mixer.

833
01:23:11,787 --> 01:23:14,627
Okay. You take
Spider-Man's pictures, right?

834
01:23:15,791 --> 01:23:17,021
l used to.

835
01:23:17,326 --> 01:23:18,376
Where is he?

836
01:23:18,660 --> 01:23:22,580
Henry and I agree. We don't see
his picture in the paper anymore.

837
01:23:25,033 --> 01:23:26,293
He...

838
01:23:28,570 --> 01:23:30,849
-...quit.
-Why?

839
01:23:32,074 --> 01:23:33,594
Wanted to try other things.

840
01:23:34,109 --> 01:23:35,399
He'll be back, right?

841
01:23:37,012 --> 01:23:38,062
I don't know.

842
01:23:39,581 --> 01:23:42,211
You'll never guess
who he wants to be.

843
01:23:43,085 --> 01:23:44,545
Spider-Man.

844
01:23:45,053 --> 01:23:48,333
-Why?
-He knows a hero when he sees one.

845
01:23:49,124 --> 01:23:52,284
Too few characters out there,
flying around like that...

846
01:23:53,028 --> 01:23:54,808
.. saving old girls like me.

847
01:23:55,197 --> 01:23:58,567
And Lord knows,
kids like Henry need a hero.

848
01:23:59,201 --> 01:24:01,721
Courageous, self-sacrificing people...

849
01:24:02,204 --> 01:24:04,224
.. setting examples for all of us.

850
01:24:05,073 --> 01:24:07,063
Everybody loves a hero.

851
01:24:07,643 --> 01:24:10,713
People line up for them.
Cheer them. Scream their names.

852
01:24:11,280 --> 01:24:14,910
And years later, they'll tell how
they stood in the rain for hours...

853
01:24:15,584 --> 01:24:17,104
.. Just to get a glimpse of the one...

854
01:24:17,452 --> 01:24:20,582
..who taught them to hold on
a second longer.

855
01:24:22,291 --> 01:24:25,101
I believe there's a hero in all of us...

856
01:24:26,328 --> 01:24:27,938
.. that keeps us honest...

857
01:24:28,730 --> 01:24:30,160
.. gives us strength...

858
01:24:30,732 --> 01:24:32,402
.. makes us noble...

859
01:24:33,702 --> 01:24:36,892
..and finally allows us to die
with pride.

860
01:24:38,473 --> 01:24:42,073
Even though sometimes
we have to be steady...

861
01:24:42,744 --> 01:24:45,174
..and give up the thing
we want the most.

862
01:24:47,316 --> 01:24:49,016
Even our dreams.

863
01:24:51,153 --> 01:24:53,433
Spider-Man did that for Henry...

864
01:24:54,089 --> 01:24:56,169
..and he wonders where he's gone.

865
01:24:57,593 --> 01:24:59,202
He needs him.

866
01:25:03,999 --> 01:25:08,039
Do you think you could lift that desk
and put it into the garage for me?

867
01:25:09,137 --> 01:25:11,036
But don't strain yourself.

868
01:25:11,440 --> 01:25:12,929
Okay.

869
01:25:31,727 --> 01:25:33,807
Strong focus on what ! want.

870
01:26:04,126 --> 01:26:05,416
I'm back!

871
01:26:05,727 --> 01:26:07,037
I'm back!

872
01:26:24,713 --> 01:26:26,023
My back.

873
01:26:27,149 --> 01:26:28,289
My back.

874
01:26:52,607 --> 01:26:56,507
Honey, you sure you don't want to
invite your friend, the photographer?

875
01:26:57,479 --> 01:26:58,559
Peter Parker?

876
01:27:01,016 --> 01:27:02,066
Positive.

877
01:27:02,417 --> 01:27:03,437
Thought he was your pal.

878
01:27:04,052 --> 01:27:06,041
-Peter Parker?
-Yeah.

879
01:27:07,255 --> 01:27:09,445
He's just a great big jerk.

880
01:27:10,125 --> 01:27:11,795
The world's full of great big jerks.

881
01:27:13,462 --> 01:27:15,042
You're adorable.

882
01:27:15,597 --> 01:27:17,057
It's just the uniform.

883
01:27:20,535 --> 01:27:22,345
Lean your head back for me.

884
01:27:23,038 --> 01:27:25,088
-Put my head back?
-Yeah, just do it.

885
01:27:27,409 --> 01:27:28,929
Just put my head back?

886
01:27:29,745 --> 01:27:31,175
Okay.

887
01:27:50,499 --> 01:27:51,869
Wow.

888
01:27:52,701 --> 01:27:54,281
I'm back on the moon.

889
01:27:59,241 --> 01:28:00,471
You up there with me?

890
01:28:21,463 --> 01:28:23,333
-Hiya.
-Surprised?

891
01:28:23,732 --> 01:28:25,102
Very.

892
01:28:25,467 --> 01:28:26,897
Thanks for coming.

893
01:28:27,369 --> 01:28:29,098
Everything okay?

894
01:28:30,338 --> 01:28:31,888
You might say so.

895
01:28:33,408 --> 01:28:36,718
This is funny.
I'm not sure how to begin.

896
01:28:39,548 --> 01:28:41,888
You know how our minds
play tricks on us.

897
01:28:42,584 --> 01:28:46,044
-Tell me about it.
-Well, mine did a real number on me.

898
01:28:48,190 --> 01:28:51,320
Some part of me heard what you
had to say after the show that night...

899
01:28:52,060 --> 01:28:55,080
.. that you were different.
But I didn't want to listen.

900
01:28:56,431 --> 01:28:58,181
l was afraid to trust you.

901
01:29:00,168 --> 01:29:02,798
But I've been thinking about it--

902
01:29:03,338 --> 01:29:06,588
Listen, there's more for me to say.

903
01:29:10,612 --> 01:29:14,242
I maybe rushed into things.
I thought--

904
01:29:15,083 --> 01:29:17,272
Wait a minute.
What are you saying?

905
01:29:18,353 --> 01:29:19,963
I'm saying...

906
01:29:26,328 --> 01:29:28,958
l thought I could be there for you,
Mary Jane...

907
01:29:29,798 --> 01:29:31,138
.. but I can't.

908
01:29:34,703 --> 01:29:37,663
My mind was playing tricks too.

909
01:29:42,677 --> 01:29:44,987
Do you love me, or not?

910
01:29:52,354 --> 01:29:53,844


911
01:29:57,259 --> 01:29:58,309
.. don't.

912
01:30:03,365 --> 01:30:05,094
You don't.

913
01:30:14,776 --> 01:30:15,976
Kiss me.

914
01:30:18,280 --> 01:30:19,509
Kiss you?

915
01:30:20,015 --> 01:30:21,505
I need to know something.

916
01:30:24,386 --> 01:30:25,846
Just one kiss.

917
01:31:13,134 --> 01:31:15,034
What's happening?

918
01:31:25,480 --> 01:31:26,969
Peter Parker...

919
01:31:28,083 --> 01:31:29,423
..and the girlfriend.

920
01:31:30,151 --> 01:31:31,791
What do you want?

921
01:31:34,689 --> 01:31:36,769
l want you to find your friend
Spider-Man.

922
01:31:37,192 --> 01:31:39,412
Tell him to meet me
at the Westside Tower at 3:00.

923
01:31:40,028 --> 01:31:41,898
I don't know where he is.

924
01:31:43,631 --> 01:31:45,001
Find him.

925
01:31:47,469 --> 01:31:49,989
Or I'll peel the flesh off her bones.

926
01:31:50,472 --> 01:31:52,251
If you lay one finger on her...

927
01:31:52,640 --> 01:31:53,900
You'll do what?

928
01:33:07,682 --> 01:33:10,992
Still no word on the whereabouts
of your son's fiancÃ©e.

929
01:33:11,619 --> 01:33:13,049
Sorry, Jonah.

930
01:33:14,322 --> 01:33:15,582
It's all my fault.

931
01:33:17,559 --> 01:33:19,699
I drove Spider-Man away.

932
01:33:20,228 --> 01:33:22,978
He was the only one who could've
stopped Octavius.

933
01:33:24,799 --> 01:33:25,999
Yes.

934
01:33:27,635 --> 01:33:30,655
Spider-Man was a hero.

935
01:33:32,240 --> 01:33:33,990
I just couldn't see it.

936
01:33:35,743 --> 01:33:37,033
He was a--

937
01:33:37,378 --> 01:33:39,748
A thief! A criminal!

938
01:33:41,583 --> 01:33:43,692
He stole my suit!
He's a menace to the entire city!

939
01:33:44,119 --> 01:33:46,779
l want that wall-crawling
arachnid prosecuted!

940
01:33:47,288 --> 01:33:49,128
I want him strung up by his web!

941
01:33:50,992 --> 01:33:53,212
I want Spider-Man!

942
01:34:22,090 --> 01:34:23,230
Where is she?

943
01:34:23,525 --> 01:34:25,894
Oh, she'll be just fine. Let's talk.

944
01:35:17,378 --> 01:35:18,428
What the hell?

945
01:37:23,571 --> 01:37:25,381
You have a train to catch.

946
01:37:28,242 --> 01:37:29,822
Help!

947
01:37:30,211 --> 01:37:33,991
Help! Help! I can't stop it!
The brakes are gone!

948
01:37:53,368 --> 01:37:55,508
-It's Spider-Man.
-Oh, my God, this is it!

949
01:37:56,104 --> 01:37:57,364
Tell everyone to hang on!

950
01:37:57,705 --> 01:37:59,255
Brace yourselves!

951
01:38:20,628 --> 01:38:22,768
Any more bright ideas?

952
01:38:23,364 --> 01:38:25,384
I got a few, yeah!

953
01:38:47,121 --> 01:38:48,551
Whoa, watch out!

954
01:39:19,454 --> 01:39:20,534
We're slowing down.

955
01:40:25,186 --> 01:40:26,915
Nice and easy, we'll go down.

956
01:40:28,155 --> 01:40:29,415
Slower. Gently.

957
01:40:34,795 --> 01:40:36,055
Is he alive?

958
01:40:40,034 --> 01:40:41,084
He's...

959
01:40:41,369 --> 01:40:42,829
Just a kid.

960
01:40:44,205 --> 01:40:45,815
No older than my son.

961
01:41:05,326 --> 01:41:06,936
It's all right.

962
01:41:11,532 --> 01:41:13,142
We found something.

963
01:41:22,710 --> 01:41:24,460
We won't tell nobody.

964
01:41:38,459 --> 01:41:40,739
It's good to have you back,
Spider-Man.

965
01:42:01,048 --> 01:42:02,538
He's mine!

966
01:42:03,584 --> 01:42:06,014
You want to get to him,
you got to go through me.

967
01:42:06,621 --> 01:42:07,911
And me.

968
01:42:08,589 --> 01:42:09,879
Me too.

969
01:42:14,996 --> 01:42:16,286
Very well.

970
01:42:45,493 --> 01:42:47,223
Where do you want him?

971
01:42:55,302 --> 01:42:56,531
And the tritium?

972
01:43:11,285 --> 01:43:12,514
Yes.

973
01:43:42,717 --> 01:43:45,376
If only could cause you the pain
that you've caused me.

974
01:43:48,556 --> 01:43:50,835
First we'll see who's behind the mask.

975
01:43:51,292 --> 01:43:53,372
I can look into your eyes as you die.

976
01:43:56,497 --> 01:43:57,897
Pete.

977
01:43:58,399 --> 01:43:59,949
No.

978
01:44:00,668 --> 01:44:01,978
It can't be.

979
01:44:08,642 --> 01:44:09,871
Harry.

980
01:44:11,479 --> 01:44:14,579
Where is she?
Where is he keeping her?

981
01:44:16,283 --> 01:44:19,793
-He's got M.J.
-No. All he wanted was the tritium.

982
01:44:21,088 --> 01:44:22,138
Tritium?

983
01:44:24,291 --> 01:44:26,041
He's making the machine again.

984
01:44:27,161 --> 01:44:30,851
When that happens, she'll die,
along with half of New York.

985
01:44:31,532 --> 01:44:33,992
-Now, where is he?
-Peter...

986
01:44:35,469 --> 01:44:37,109
.. you killed my father.

987
01:44:42,476 --> 01:44:46,045
There are bigger things
happening here than me and you.

988
01:44:47,314 --> 01:44:49,774
Harry, please, I've got to stop him.

989
01:45:00,661 --> 01:45:02,181
Hey!

990
01:45:03,464 --> 01:45:04,954
Hey!

991
01:45:06,534 --> 01:45:08,114
I'm talking to you!

992
01:45:08,602 --> 01:45:11,732
You got what you needed for your little
science project, now let me go.

993
01:45:12,339 --> 01:45:13,979
I can't let you go,
you'd bring the police.

994
01:45:14,375 --> 01:45:16,655
Not that anybody could stop me
now that Spider-Man's dead.

995
01:45:17,778 --> 01:45:19,118
He's not dead.

996
01:45:19,547 --> 01:45:21,887
-I don't believe you.
-Believe it.

997
01:45:40,034 --> 01:45:41,174
Surprise.

998
01:45:45,706 --> 01:45:47,166
As soon as you get free--

999
01:45:49,543 --> 01:45:53,003
I should have known Osborn
wouldn't have the spine to finish you!

1000
01:45:53,614 --> 01:45:56,273
Shut it down, Ock. You're going
to hurt a lot more people this time.

1001
01:45:57,017 --> 01:45:59,007
Well, that's a risk
we're willing to take.

1002
01:46:00,421 --> 01:46:02,061
Well, I'm not.

1003
01:46:34,755 --> 01:46:35,925
Hang on, Mary Jane!

1004
01:46:52,072 --> 01:46:53,122
Run!

1005
01:47:17,731 --> 01:47:19,871
Let's see you scurry out of this.

1006
01:47:44,058 --> 01:47:45,988
Now what?

1007
01:48:16,323 --> 01:48:18,163
Dr. Octavius.

1008
01:48:21,628 --> 01:48:22,648
We have to shut it down.

1009
01:48:23,664 --> 01:48:25,094
Please tell me how.

1010
01:48:25,466 --> 01:48:26,806
Peter Parker?

1011
01:48:30,471 --> 01:48:32,250
"Brilliant but lazy."

1012
01:48:32,773 --> 01:48:34,083
Look at what's happening.

1013
01:48:35,275 --> 01:48:36,915
We must destroy it.

1014
01:48:42,683 --> 01:48:44,143
Il can't destroy it.

1015
01:48:49,590 --> 01:48:50,850
I won't.

1016
01:48:56,497 --> 01:48:58,397
You once spoke to me
about intelligence.

1017
01:49:00,567 --> 01:49:03,877
That it was a gift to be used
for the good of mankind.

1018
01:49:06,073 --> 01:49:07,243
A privilege.

1019
01:49:08,142 --> 01:49:10,802
These things have turned you
into something you're not.

1020
01:49:12,212 --> 01:49:13,852
Don't listen to them.

1021
01:49:19,987 --> 01:49:21,277
It was my dream.

1022
01:49:21,622 --> 01:49:25,632
Sometimes, to do what's right,
we have to be steady...

1023
01:49:26,326 --> 01:49:28,466
..and give up the thing
we want the most.

1024
01:49:29,630 --> 01:49:31,120
Even our dreams.

1025
01:49:37,371 --> 01:49:38,831
You're right.

1026
01:49:46,380 --> 01:49:48,020
He's right.

1027
01:49:50,050 --> 01:49:51,360
Listen.

1028
01:49:53,720 --> 01:49:55,800
Listen to me now.

1029
01:49:59,026 --> 01:50:01,016
Listen to me now.

1030
01:50:05,065 --> 01:50:07,674
Now, tell me how to stop it.

1031
01:50:09,136 --> 01:50:10,476
It can't be stopped.

1032
01:50:12,206 --> 01:50:13,956
It's self-sustaining now.

1033
01:50:14,408 --> 01:50:16,218
-Think!
-Unless....

1034
01:50:18,078 --> 01:50:19,508
The river.

1035
01:50:21,181 --> 01:50:22,491
Drown it.

1036
01:50:24,651 --> 01:50:25,911
I'll do it.

1037
01:51:11,365 --> 01:51:13,825
No!

1038
01:51:26,146 --> 01:51:27,456
Hi.

1039
01:51:28,382 --> 01:51:29,842
Hi.

1040
01:51:30,751 --> 01:51:32,091
This is really heavy.

1041
01:51:56,777 --> 01:51:58,477
M.J.

1042
01:52:01,582 --> 01:52:03,012
You do love me.

1043
01:52:03,717 --> 01:52:04,887
Ido.

1044
01:52:06,053 --> 01:52:07,863
Even though you said you didn't.

1045
01:52:11,058 --> 01:52:13,168
I will not die a monster.

1046
01:53:18,659 --> 01:53:20,438
I think I always knew...

1047
01:53:21,762 --> 01:53:23,251
.all this time...

1048
01:53:24,598 --> 01:53:26,208
..who you really were.

1049
01:53:27,100 --> 01:53:29,270
Then you know
why we can't be together.

1050
01:53:30,737 --> 01:53:33,287
Spider-Man will always have enemies.

1051
01:53:35,575 --> 01:53:37,974
I can't let you take that risk.

1052
01:53:43,083 --> 01:53:44,223
I will...

1053
01:53:46,119 --> 01:53:48,049
.. always be Spider-Man.

1054
01:53:51,124 --> 01:53:53,174
You and I can never be.

1055
01:54:41,775 --> 01:54:43,525
Mary Jane!

1056
01:55:47,040 --> 01:55:48,380
Hello?

1057
01:56:04,591 --> 01:56:05,851
Who's that?

1058
01:56:06,159 --> 01:56:07,888
Son.

1059
01:56:09,196 --> 01:56:10,336
I'm here.

1060
01:56:11,765 --> 01:56:13,255
Dad?

1061
01:56:14,534 --> 01:56:16,404
-l thought you were--
-No.

1062
01:56:17,270 --> 01:56:19,080
I'm alive in you, Harry.

1063
01:56:19,506 --> 01:56:20,556
Now it's your turn.

1064
01:56:22,342 --> 01:56:24,682
You swore to make Spider-Man pay.

1065
01:56:25,345 --> 01:56:26,835
Now make him pay.

1066
01:56:27,481 --> 01:56:28,971
But Pete's my best friend.

1067
01:56:29,382 --> 01:56:30,611
And I'm your father.

1068
01:56:31,785 --> 01:56:33,125
You're weak.

1069
01:56:34,321 --> 01:56:38,101
You were always weak. You'll always
be weak until you take control.

1070
01:56:39,659 --> 01:56:42,179
Now you know the truth about Peter.

1071
01:56:43,497 --> 01:56:44,867
Be strong, Harry.

1072
01:56:46,099 --> 01:56:47,269
Avenge me.

1073
01:56:50,303 --> 01:56:52,083
-Avenge me!
-No!

1074
01:59:17,017 --> 01:59:18,187
Call Deborah.

1075
01:59:18,485 --> 01:59:20,125
The caterer?

1076
01:59:21,354 --> 01:59:23,164
Tell her not to open the caviar.

1077
02:00:04,764 --> 02:00:06,784
Had to do what I had to do.

1078
02:00:08,635 --> 02:00:09,895
Mary Jane.

1079
02:00:11,204 --> 02:00:12,284
Peter.

1080
02:00:13,640 --> 02:00:15,860
l can't survive without you.

1081
02:00:26,152 --> 02:00:27,792
You shouldn't be here.

1082
02:00:29,122 --> 02:00:31,782
I know you think we can't be together.

1083
02:00:33,259 --> 02:00:36,359
But can't you respect me enough
to let me make my own decision?

1084
02:00:38,198 --> 02:00:39,838
I know there'll be risks.

1085
02:00:40,767 --> 02:00:43,077
But I want to face them with you.

1086
02:00:44,537 --> 02:00:47,607
It's wrong that
we should only be half-alive...

1087
02:00:48,174 --> 02:00:49,604
.. half of ourselves.

1088
02:00:52,345 --> 02:00:53,805
Il love you.

1089
02:00:56,249 --> 02:00:58,858
So here lam,
standing in your doorway.

1090
02:01:00,987 --> 02:01:03,707
I've always been
standing in your doorway.

1091
02:01:11,131 --> 02:01:14,151
Isn't it about time somebody
saved your life?

1092
02:01:20,540 --> 02:01:22,150
Well, say something.

1093
02:01:24,778 --> 02:01:27,028
Thank you, Mary Jane Watson.

1094
02:01:43,530 --> 02:01:45,110
Go get them, tiger.

